			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>31<hi rend="sup">st</hi>. Augt. <hi rend="underline">5608</hi></date></p>
			<p>Revd Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Having determined to return to <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName><lb/> from hence by way of the <placeName>Lakes</placeName> I beg to trouble you with the<lb/> <sic>niclosed</sic><add>&#63;</add>&#44; my offerings at synagogue.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have had the pleasure of seeing none <persName>Abm Hart</persName><lb/> of your city&#44; it appears he has not yet perused &#8220;<sic>Aretrospect</sic>&#8221;<lb/> he has promised to procure a copy from you.  As you were so<lb/> kind as to say you would return the 50 copies I transmitted you<lb/> to see what could be done with them permit me to remind you<lb/> of the same &#38; to request your exertions to place them.  Should you<lb/> require any more copies on writing me at <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> I will<lb/> forward them to you</p>
			<p>I find the object I left for the consideration<lb/> of the <placeName>Crosby St.</placeName> Synagogue Trustees has not yet been formally<lb/> brought under their notice for want of a quorum&#8212;a promise<lb/> is given that it shall not be neglected but I cannot say I<lb/> am very sanguine as to the result</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I am reverend Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Your obt Servant</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">A A. Lindo</persName></p>
			<p>If you write me have the </p>
			<p>goodness to direct to me </p>
			<p>at <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>.&#95;</p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          
